title: Enemy
subTitle: Rajiv grows envious of his childhood friend, Chozhan, as he is better than him at most things. The frenemies grow apart only to meet under very different circumstances several years later.

title: Vicky Donor
subTitle: Vicky, a lively young man, works as a sperm donor for Dr Baldev Chaddha and proves to be highly successful. Consequently, Baldev's clinic thrives with the help of Vicky's contributions.

title: Namaste England
subTitle: Param and Jasmeet fall in love and get married. However, things get complicated when Jasmeet wishes to relocate to London and establish her career.

title: The Dunes
subTitle: When a journalist moves to his hometown, he does not have the slightest idea that the strings of his unresolved past are lying there in wait to entangle him in a psychological Gordian knot.

title: Mahabharat

title: Race
subTitle: The relationship between two stepbrothers develops cracks when they fall in love with the same woman. As a result, the younger brother tries to kill the other and inherit the insurance money.

title: Radhe Shyam
subTitle: Despite being a doctor with no inclination towards superstitious beliefs, Prerana places her love and faith in Aditya, a palmist whose predictions turn out to be too spot-on to be disregarded.

title: Kisi Ka Bhai Kisi Ki Jaan
subTitle: Bhaijaan, the eldest of three siblings, refuses to get married to maintain harmony in his family. However, complications arise after his brothers conspire for him to fall in love.

title: Baby John

title: Jai Ho
